  <div class="mt-8 grid grid-cols-1 gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
    <div>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold"><a href="/bridge-fen/">BRIDGE FEN</a></h3>
      <div class="prose-page mt-2">
        <p>
          Our largest association site with over 100 tenants, the Bridge Fen site is just outside
          the City off the A142 Stuntney Causeway. It is the only Ely site that has the famous
          black fen soil, earning the nickname 'giant growbag'.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold"><a href="/canterbury-avenue/">CANTERBURY AVENUE</a></h3>
      <div class="prose-page mt-2">
        <p>
          One of our smallest sites with about a dozen plotholders, this is a former playground
          which was derelict and unloved, but is now a thriving community.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold"><a href="/new-barns/">NEW BARNS</a></h3>
      <div class="prose-page mt-2">
        <p>
          New Barns is our largest site within the City. It currently has 58 tenants, and is
          located in New Barns Avenue next to the City cemetery behind the playing field. Most
          plots are 5 or 10 poles in area.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold"><a href="/upherds-lane/">UPHERDS LANE</a></h3>
      <div class="prose-page mt-2">
        <p>
          Upherds is a smaller site than New Barns, with 45 tenants. The site is triangular with a
          patchwork of plots, most of which are subdivisions of the original 10 pole plot layout.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="rents" class="mt-12 text-2xl font-bold">Plot Rents</h2>

  <div class="prose-page mt-4">
    <p>
      The annual rent on all allotment plots is due on 1 October. Charges are based on area
      occupied, and are the same for all sites. Full details of amounts and how to pay are
      notified to tenant plotholders in September by email or by letter. The table of annual rent
      charges (shown below) for 2025/26 was agreed at the March 2025 Association AGM. There is no
      change in annual rents from 2024/25.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-6 overflow-x-auto">
